  "prompt": "What is the proper way to use RSVP out of the following?",
  "response": "\"RSVP\" is derived from the French phrase \"r\u00e9pondez s'il vous pla\u00eet,\" which means \"please respond.\" It\u2019s used to request that invited guests let the host know whether they will attend an event. \n\nThe proper way to use \"RSVP\" is as follows:\n\n1. **In Invitations**: You can include RSVP in the invitation to indicate that you want guests to confirm their attendance. Common phrasings include:\n   - \"Please RSVP by [date].\"\n   - \"Kindly RSVP to [contact information].\"\n\n2. **As a Verb**: When you respond to an invitation, you can say:\n   - \"I will RSVP to the invitation.\"\n   - \"I RSVPed that I will attend.\"\n\n3. **When Telling Others**: If you're informing someone about attending or not attending an event, you can say:\n   - \"I received an RSVP from John indicating he will attend.\"\n   - \"Please make sure to RSVP so we know how many to expect.\"\n\nIn summary, \"RSVP\" can function as a request in invitations, as an action verb when confirming attendance, or refer to the response itself.",
